tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated blood glucose, creatinine, alkaline phosphatase, and borderline high cholesterol, suggesting impaired renal function, possible diabetes or poor glycemic control, mild cholestasis or bone turnover, and increased cardiovascular risk. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal and metabolic status and further evaluation as indicated.
